#DESCRIPTION The Guardians of Law are a regimented force, divided by their home town
and time served.  

Guardians are based in their hometowns, and hold jurisdiction there.  A
native guardian can overturn a mark made by a non-native Guardian of equal
or lesser rank, if he feels it is unjust and incorrect.  The native
Guardians of a given town are lead by the town Leader, if one exists.  The
Guardian Leader of a town holds final judgement on all marks in his city,
and answers only to the Guardian Leader in matters of his guarded city.  

The Leader of House Guardian holds final judgement in all marks.  

Guardians who have served the Halls of Law for twenty years are marked as
Senior Guardians, and hold rank over those who have not served at least
twenty years.  Those who have served for fifty years are known as Elder
Guardians, and hold rank over those who have not served at least over fifty
years.  The Town Leaders and the Guardian Leader hold rank over Elder and
Senior guardians.  

A Town Leader can enter without violence the guilds of his city by speaking
the words 'Allow me entrance.  ' The Leader of the Guardians may access
guilds in any city in this way as well.  This power is to be used ONLY in
the pursuit of criminals.  Abuse of this for any other reason will result in
removal from house Guardian.  
